# Azuga Installation Platform

A scalable, enterprise-ready vehicle installation guide platform for GPS, SafetyCAM, ELD, and Asset Tracker devices.

## 🎯 Features

### Version 1.0
- **Authentication**: Admin and Installer role-based access
- **Vehicle Library**: Search by Make, Model, Year, VIN
- **Device Support**: GPS, SafetyCAM, ELD, Asset Tracker
- **Interactive 2D Guides**: Clickable hotspots, animated cable routing
- **Progress Tracking**: Mark steps complete, auto-save, resume later
- **Admin Portal**: Manage vehicles, steps, images, videos, hotspots
- **Installer Dashboard**: Recent installations, favorites, search
- **Reports**: Installation history, completion metrics
- **Mobile First**: Fully responsive design

### Future Features
- 3D vehicle visualization (Three.js integration ready)
- Advanced analytics
- Real-time collaboration
- Multi-language support
- Cloud storage integration

## 🏗️ Architecture

```
azuga-installation-platform/
├── backend/                    # Node.js/Express API
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── config/            # Configuration (db, auth)
│   │   ├── controllers/        # Route handlers
│   │   ├── models/            # Data models
│   │   ├── routes/            # API routes
│   │   ├── middleware/        # Auth, validation
│   │   ├── services/          # Business logic
│   │   ├── utils/             # Helpers
│   │   └── index.ts           # Entry point
│   ├── migrations/            # Database migrations
│   ├── seeds/                 # Database seeds
│   ├── .env.example
│   ├── tsconfig.json
│   └── package.json
├── frontend/                   # React + TypeScript
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── components/        # Reusable components
│   │   ├── pages/             # Page components
│   │   ├── features/          # Feature modules
│   │   ├── hooks/             # Custom React hooks
│   │   ├── services/          # API client
│   │   ├── store/             # State management
│   │   ├── styles/            # Tailwind config
│   │   ├── types/             # TypeScript types
│   │   ├── utils/             # Helper functions
│   │   ├── App.tsx
│   │   └── main.tsx
│   ├── .env.example
│   ├── tailwind.config.js
│   ├── vite.config.ts
│   └── package.json
├── docker-compose.yml         # Local dev environment
├── .gitignore
└── DEVELOPMENT.md             # Setup guide
```

## 🚀 Quick Start

See [DEVELOPMENT.md](./DEVELOPMENT.md) for detailed setup instructions.

## 🔄 API Architecture

The API is designed to support future 3D integration:
- All vehicle data includes geometry-ready metadata
- Installation steps reference 2D/3D coordinates
- Hotspots and cable routes use parametric definitions
- Easy to add Three.js viewer without data model changes

## 📦 Technology Stack

- **Frontend**: React 18, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Vite
- **Backend**: Node.js, Express, TypeScript
- **Database**: PostgreSQL
- **Storage**: Local (S3-ready architecture)
- **Auth**: JWT + Role-based access control

